OL,3,CQuarter of motorists affected by
OL,4,Cbright headlights have cut night
OL,5,Cdriving
OL,7,FAround 17% of night-time drivers say
OL,8,Fbright headlights make them feel
OL,9,Ffatigued, while 16% report headaches,
OL,10,Fmigraines or eye pain.
OL,12,FDepartment for Transport (DfT) figures
OL,13,Fshow that since 2013, bright
OL,14,Fheadlights have been a contributory
OL,15,Ffactor in an average of 280 crashes
OL,16,Fevery year on Britain's roads,
OL,17,Fincluding six fatal accidents annually.
